Oh.

1199
01:33:52,759 --> 01:33:53,953
Oh, Adelle?

1200
01:33:54,142 --> 01:33:55,575
[Muttering]

1201
01:33:56,244 --> 01:33:57,244
Adelle?

1202
01:34:06,354 --> 01:34:07,597
[Buzzing]

1203
01:34:08,356 --> 01:34:09,356
[Buzzing]

1204
01:34:09,424 --> 01:34:10,624
[Gasping]

1205
01:34:19,000 --> 01:34:20,210
[Grunting]

1206
01:34:28,428 --> 01:34:29,918
Mrs. Hill?

1207
01:34:30,430 --> 01:34:31,624
Yes, I am.

1208
01:34:31,698 --> 01:34:35,293
I'm Detective Sergeant West
from Braddock.

1209
01:34:36,636 --> 01:34:38,433
May I come in, please?

1210
01:34:39,706 --> 01:34:41,799
Yes, of course.

1211
01:34:43,143 --> 01:34:44,474
Thank you.

1212
01:34:48,315 --> 01:34:52,547
Is Mrs. Bruckner here?
Because this concerns her, too.

1213
01:34:52,686 --> 01:34:55,849
- No. I'm afraid she's out at the moment.
- I see.

1214
01:34:56,289 --> 01:34:58,723
Well, Mrs. Hill, I wonder if you might...

1215
01:34:58,892 --> 01:35:02,020
...mind looking at this photograph
that I have here.

1216
01:35:02,229 --> 01:35:03,457
Certainly.

1217
01:35:12,405 --> 01:35:13,667
You don't know him?

1218
01:35:14,474 --> 01:35:15,498
No.

1219
01:35:15,775 --> 01:35:18,539
- You've never seen him before?
- No.

1220
01:35:18,845 --> 01:35:23,282
They found his body just three days ago
in that trench right across the street there.

1221
01:35:23,950 --> 01:35:25,850
Yes, that dreadful accident.

1222
01:35:25,986 --> 01:35:27,647
He knew Ellie Banner.

1223
01:35:28,655 --> 01:35:31,920
He was her lover.

1224
01:35:34,761 --> 01:35:37,491
What an extraordinary coincidence.

1225
01:35:37,664 --> 01:35:38,961
I see.

1226
01:35:39,733 --> 01:35:42,224
<i>I see, that's why you thought that...</i>

1227
01:35:44,871 --> 01:35:47,567
I'm sorry, Sergeant, I can't help you.

1228
01:35:50,944 --> 01:35:53,310
Mrs. Hill, didn't you or Mrs. Bruckner...

1229
01:35:53,380 --> 01:35:55,848
...ever receive any
threatening telephone calls?

1230
01:35:56,316 --> 01:35:57,874
Why, no.

1231
01:35:59,552 --> 01:36:01,850
It's a thing they often do.

1232
01:36:02,222 --> 01:36:03,280
Who?

1233
01:36:04,591 --> 01:36:07,788
Well, the important thing is,
you're out of danger now.

1234
01:36:08,028 --> 01:36:09,120
I am?

1235
01:36:10,730 --> 01:36:12,755
That's always nice to know.

1236
01:36:14,034 --> 01:36:15,968
Wait a minute, Sergeant.

1237
01:36:16,736 --> 01:36:19,170
<i>You mean, Ms. Stuart...</i>

1238
01:36:19,673 --> 01:36:21,766
I mean, Mrs. Bruckner...

1239
01:36:22,542 --> 01:36:27,445
...and myself were in danger
from this man who loved Ellie Banner?

1240
01:36:27,814 --> 01:36:30,146
Yes, from what he said
to a couple of people...

1241
01:36:30,216 --> 01:36:32,582
...he was crazy with the idea of revenge.

1242
01:36:32,652 --> 01:36:35,416
Of course,
he suffered greatly when she died.

1243
01:36:35,488 --> 01:36:40,152
Your boys were out of reach, of course,
and so he fixed on their mothers.

1244
01:36:41,127 --> 01:36:43,322
He traced you out here.

1245
01:36:50,136 --> 01:36:52,764
I think you've had a very lucky escape.

1246
01:36:55,809 --> 01:36:56,798
Yes.

1247
01:36:58,745 --> 01:37:00,610
It's all been quite a shock.

1248
01:37:02,649 --> 01:37:04,480
I can't stand violence.

1249
01:37:04,951 --> 01:37:06,441
It's unforgivable.

1250
01:37:07,387 --> 01:37:10,117
<i>You see, Sergeant,
that's why when my boy...</i>

1251
01:37:13,026 --> 01:37:15,551
Do you mind
